# Vue Composables & Lifecycle

> Vue composables (`useX`) — not Cursor hooks runtime.

## Lifecycle

- `onMounted` / `onUnmounted` for DOM subscriptions
- `onBeforeUnmount` for cleanup before tear-down
- Avoid async setup without handling cancellation

## Watchers

- Prefer `watch` with explicit source over `watchEffect` when dependencies are unclear
- Use `watchOnce` for one-time initialization when appropriate
- Debounce expensive watchers on user input

## Reactivity pitfalls

- Do not destructure `reactive()` without `toRefs`
- Use `shallowRef` for large immutable objects when deep tracking is unnecessary
- `ref` in template auto-unwraps; in script use `.value`

## Async

- Race: abort previous fetch in composable when id/query changes
- Loading / error state as explicit refs, not implicit globals
